Plumbing notes:
  - The dry_run_summary event fires from teardownRuntime BEFORE the
    publisher closes. That's the same hook used by Phase G.2 for
    `session_teardown`.
  - opencode-plugin's resolveBinding now SELECTs cloud_runs.dry_run via
    the LEFT JOIN it already uses for automation_id. Worker startup
    overhead is identical; no extra query.
  - The buffer lives on ctx, NOT in a module-level singleton, so the
    pool-task pattern (one worker container handling multiple opencode
    sessions over its 15-min idle ceiling) won't cross-contaminate dry
    runs between sessions.
  - Approval bypass is desirable for dry-run because the operator
    seeing the preview IS the approval — they decide whether to activate
    afterwards. Saves the dry-run from sitting in the approvals.gate
    LISTEN/NOTIFY loop for 4 hours.
  - The mutating-composio regex is broader than B.8's destructive
    denylist on purpose: dry-run wants to catch ALL outbound writes
    (CREATE_EVENT is fine in production but should be buffered in dry).

Out of scope (lands in E.8):
  - The API path that actually flips a run to dry_run=true. POST
    /v1/automations/:id/dry-run + the worker dispatch wiring lands in
    E.8. E.7 only provides the in-worker side of the contract.
  - Activate endpoint + draft-status semantics on CRUD also E.8.
